RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 94. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 25000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile O r Over Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances). If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGH HEATER saved ground through the turns when never far back, guided into the three path for the drive, gained the lead inside the sixteenth pole and held. ENGLISH CHALLENGE was in the three or four path through the far turn, swung into the lane from the five or six path and rallied from mid-track to just miss. CASANOVA KITTEN stalked the pace from the two path through the far turn, bid into the lane two wide, gained a clear lead with an eighth to go then yielded late. GREY STREAK was along the inside early, moved in the lane from the four path, angled in to the two path and was gaining to the end. MAJOR SPARKS trailed for three-quarter, angled into the five path for the drive and gained belatedly from mid-track. NEPAL UP never a factor while saving ground. ENGLISH TIDE set the pace while near the inside through the turn then gave way. PADDY'S HOUSE raced in the three path while in mid-pack, came into the lane four wide and tired. BARRISTER TOM chased the pace from the three path, moved three wide through the turn when not far back then was empty into the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: High Heater
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground turns, guided 3path, in time

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STICKER pressed the pace outside of the leader, bid late and was clear late under mild urging. SNERDLEY saved ground, then bid late between rivals. MYSTERY IMPACT stalked the pace in the five path and offered a mild late bid. SIR RONALDO led inside before giving way late. RACING IN MY HEART stalked the pace in the three path before fading late. SAN RONIN raced evenly inside. BLAME IT ON MILLER was through early outside.

ENTRY.NAME: Sticker
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace outside leader,bid late,clear,mild urging

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 1/16 on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OH POLLYANNA saved ground through the far turn when not far back, guided into the three path into the lane then finished with good energy to clear late. FLURR was unhurried while near the inside, gained momentum in late turn, angled into the five path for the drive and finished willingly to be second best. MADRE DI GRANDEZZA was in the two path through the turn, bid into the lane from the three path, had aim on the top ones with an eighth to go but lacked the needed response. MISS BRIGHTSIDE pressed the pace two wide down the backstretch and into the turn, bid into the lane, gained a clear lead with an eighth to go and weakened late. BELLA MORNING raced in the four path through the far turn when near the back, came into the lane from the seven path and moved up a spot while never a threat. ARTEMUS SWEETHEART trailed into the far turn while near the rail, came off the rail through late turn, came into the lane from the five path and passed tired ones. BLUE BLUE BAYOU chased the pace along the inside into the far turn, was asked for more near the three-eighths pole then tired through the lane. DARTIGA set the pace along the inside through mid-turn then was done entering the lane. GET STORM AWAY chased the pace from the three path into the far turn then faded. LADYONTHEHILL not far behind while off the inside into the far turn, was asked for more after mid-turn and was suddenly done.

ENTRY.OWNER: Borchetta Mike Borchetta Martha and Borchetta Scott

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3path turn, asked turn, done late turn

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COWBOY IMAGE stalked the pace in the four path, bid at the three-eighths pole and was clear late under steady urging. PHILIP SNOW was clear early but couldn't hold off the winner. FOREVER FRIENDS stalked the pace in the two path, bid at the three-eighths pole but couldn't close late. REITERATION raced evenly in the four path. TANEYCOMO saved ground to no avail. MAMA'S BOY was through early. WINNIETHEPOOMOMENT saved ground to no avail. GENERAL AFFAIR was not a factor. BIGLEY HUGE faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 Indiana bre d maidens and claiming races for $12,500 or less not considered in eligibility. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADMIRAL RETURNS was well back early while unhurried, began moving closer into the far turn while coming off the inside, bid four wide in late turn while continuing to gain momentum, swung in the lane from the five or six path then swept past. VERSATILE was in the three path through the far turn when near the back, continued in the three path entering the lane, guided to the five path and finished with good energy. TIZ A BEAST chased the pace from the three path through the far turn, was asked for more approaching the quarter pole, moved closest to the leader into the lane then was no match for the top two. SHAZIER trailed into the far turn, angled into the eight path and moved up while not a threat. FIERCE ASSAULT saved ground into the lane, was asked for more into the lane then weakened late. MAMBA FOREVER raced three wide through the far turn when a contender, came into the lane from the four path and weakened. PLAIN OR PEANUT set the pace along the inside then gave way entering the lane. PONTI PRIDE saved ground into the lane and tired. EVEN MONEY never a factor while off the inside. MOON MISCHIEF pressed the pace two wide through the far turn then was empty through the lane. The race was hand-timed due to a timer malfunction.

ENTRY.OWNER: Willowbrook Stables Ltd (Neiman) and Woods Jane

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINSTON WOLF saved ground, shifted to the four path at the quarter pole, rallied and drew off under steady urging. INTO IT angled inside early, stalked the pace inside, dueled outside of the leader, bid at the quarter pole, then yielded in the stretch. MY UNCLE FRANK was squeezed back at the start, was never far back and gained the show spot late. RIGHTEOUS FREEDOM stalked the pace in the three path, then faded in the stretch. RAMSEY bumped a foe at the start, then improved position late. CAMBIASO passed tired rivals. BOOGIE BODE stalked the pace in the three path, then faded in the stretch. SON OF A GRAY was bumped at the start, went clear early, dueled inside to the stretch and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANISA was off to an alert start to gain the lead at once, cleared well before the first call, continued clear under a snug hold, widened into the lane, was roused three times inside the eighth pole and extended the end. CHROME RACER was along the inside through the turn, came off the inside into the lane, was under a strong drive late and just got up for the place spot while in the three path. SUPER CHRISTIE chased the pace while in the three path through the turn, came into the lane from the four path with aim on the leader then weakened late and lost the place spot. PREEMPT saved ground through the turn and into the lane when never far back, raced in the two path through the final eighth and was outfinished for the place and show spot. HONORABLE WOMAN was in the three or four path through the turn, came into the lane from the five path and proved to not be a threat. GRAY VIXEN stumbled badly at the start, raced near the back while in the two path , came into the lane from the three path and never was a factor. AIRFORCE ANNIE chased the pace from the four path into the turn then steadily faded.
